Let's put it this way, this major will recruit 100 students, and
there are 130 students applying for this major. First, 110 people will
be admitted, and then 20 will be withdrawn. In this way, those
after 90 will be transferred to other majors. , In fact, this major
has not recruited 100 people, but only 90 people, so 10 places are
reserved. Although enrollment is apparently over at this time, it is
just the end of unified enrollment. If enrollment data is released at
this time, it will definitely not work because not enough people
have been recruited and the data cannot be released. The remaining
10 places are reserved places. Some of them are transferred
from other majors if they are relevant, or they are directly arranged
for those who are relevant. If it were announced at that time, there
would definitely be a lot of attention. One year later, the college
entrance examination Now that the dust has settled, no one
will pay attention to what happened last year.

比起国内的很多事，高考已经是非常公正公开了；横向比较美国的大学申请，中国高考更是公平的典范了。有批评、允许批评都是进步，也别苛求了，水至清则无鱼。想想把教育公平标榜为logo的美国大学，legacy、DEI，各种无可量化的标准不说，就AO轻飘飘的一句：你希望大学都是一模一样的学生吗？就让多少学生无所适从。标准清晰哪怕再刁钻都有努力的方向；不明确的暗箱操作、主观喜好让大学申请成为玄学，所谓“不一样”如何定义？谁来定义？留10%机动名额，比起录取总统女儿、州长儿子、巨额捐款人的孙子、把革命口号写满一页的小将，已经很可以理解了。

When I was in school, there was a first-tier major who always boasted that he had a high IQ. He
clamored to take the TOEFL test in his freshman year, but he took the test four times for all four
levels before he passed. Later, a student who used to study hacking software actually hacked into
a database in the school and could see the college entrance examination scores of all students in
the school. I specifically checked this student's scores and was shocked. His college entrance
examination score was only over 360 points, let alone a single one. In this line, even two books
were not enough, but he actually started taking the first line major in his freshman year. At that time,
I was surprised how he was admitted to the university. It turns out that if you don’t have enough
scores, if you can get into university, you don’t have to be restricted by one or two books at all!
